summary: Rumors of a ZSS blaster replica have been circulating. It was briefly listed online at GameStop, but it quickly disappeared. I...
body:
Rumors of a ZSS blaster replica have been circulating. It was briefly listed online at GameStop, but it quickly disappeared. I can now confirm that GameStop is accepting preorders for them in store. No picture has been released, but it’s safe to say it’s based on this image. It’s set to release on August 9th for $60.

Use this item number to help your GameStop employee find it in the system: 195736 042/00

summary: This may be old news, but I wanted to wait to confirm it before sharing. On September 15th, a Samus Returns collector’s box will...
body: This may be old news, but I wanted to wait to confirm it before sharing. On September 15th, a Samus Returns collector’s box will be released for $50. It’s not listed online in America, so you need to go into your local GameStop to preorder it. Canada had a listing on EB Games but it seems the link doesn’t work.

blog.name: thegreenestofbeans
blog.title: And Now, Ducks
blog.description: Hi! I’m just some kid with a green hoodie permanently fused onto her who is still learning how to use this site. In the meantime, I’ll just occasionally post terrible art and unoriginal edits and analyses of my own while also liking and reblogging cool discussions, trashy memes, and other people’s much more beautiful art on my side blog, @greenbean-quack. For the time being, you can just call me bean, green bean, GB (Gibi if you want to make it more name-like, I guess :P) or whatever works (idk). Btw I’m a weirdo who worships Ducks. Other things include SU, Gravity Falls, Nintendo, Looney Tunes, Animaniacs, SVTFOE, TAWOG, etc. (but for now you’ll pretty much only see Ducktales here because it’s my current obsession.)
